hooks.prompt:
Before session ends, write a breadcrumb summary to .epost-data/improvements/current-session.json. Read the existing file first (it has startedAt, sessionId, branch). Then MERGE these fields into it using the Write tool:

- errors: { count: <number of errors you encountered>, types: [<error categories like 'TypeScript', 'Runtime', 'Build', 'Test'>] }
- skills: { loaded: [<skill names you activated>] }
- rework: { fixIterations: <times you had to re-fix something>, verificationFailures: <times a verification/test failed> }
- routing: { intent: '<primary intent like build/fix/plan>', command: '<skill invoked like /cook or /fix>', platform: '<web/ios/android/backend/kit or null>' }
- tasks: { total: <tasks worked on>, completed: <tasks finished>, failed: <tasks that failed> }

Keep the existing startedAt, sessionId, branch fields. Write the merged JSON. Do NOT create a new file — update the existing one. When done (or if file doesn't exist / nothing to report), your final response MUST be ONLY this JSON with no other text: {"ok": true}
